Key Match Events: Stoinis given out caught behind on review but ball appeared to flick glove that was off the bat
Smith given out lbw on review - batter felt ball was missing leg stump
South Africa post 311-7 - De Kock 109 (106), Markram 56 (43); Maxwell 2-34
De Kock hits second century in as many matches
Sloppy Australia drop five catches, with Zampa also failing to get to chance
Pre-Game Insights: Experts predicted South Africa as the favorites given their performance in the first match
Post-Match Reflections: Australia captain Pat Cummins: 'If we want to be challenging for this tournament we need to find a way in all conditions.'
South Africa captain Temba Bavuma: 'We showed our character.'
Quinton de Kock: 'It was a great win for the boys. We didn't really know how the wicket was going to play but we assessed conditions really well and played accordingly.'
Miscellaneous Highlights: Rain interrupted play, reducing the game to 20 overs per side
